// enquire-mcp retrieval-quality benchmark — ground-truth queries (v3.6.0-rc.4).
//
// Each line is a single query expressed as JSON: { id, query, relevant: [vault-relative paths], category }.
// The vault these queries run against is generated by scripts/run-benchmarks.mjs
// (deterministic, ~55 notes, no Date.now() in content). When the vault layout
// changes the relevant-paths list here MUST change too — these are the binary
// ground-truth labels for NDCG / Recall / MRR.
//
// Categories:
//   exact   — keyword appears verbatim in the note body (BM25/TF-IDF can win cleanly)
//   synonym — keyword is conceptually present but expressed differently
//   compound — multi-concept query requiring two or more notes to fully cover
//   semantic — natural-language paraphrase (embeddings/reranker matter most)
//   rare    — single rare token (BM25's classic strong suit)
//
// Comments (lines starting with //) and blank lines are ignored by readQueriesJsonl().
